        • [ - ] jesper - member since 13-Feb-15

          @jesper For those of you who don't check it out this is a cut-out from EUFA's official statement of this change of rules (4. august): "Following the changes approved by the UEFA Executive Committee on 17 June 2020 on the format of the 2019/20 UEFA Champions League and 2019/20 UEFA Europa League, the remaining stages of these competitions have reduced the quarter-finals and semi-finals rounds to single-leg matches. In order to recreate the same balance of matches left after the removal of pending yellow cards, the UEFA Executive Committee has decided to anticipate the cut-off date for yellow cards received by players and staff after the Round of 16 instead of after the quarter-finals (i.e. two matches before the final)".
